.TH "xdr_buf_subsegment" 9 "xdr_buf_subsegment" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xdr_buf_subsegment \- set subbuf to a portion of buf
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xdr_buf_subsegment
.BI "(const struct xdr_buf *buf "  ","
.BI "struct xdr_buf *subbuf "  ","
.BI "unsigned int base "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
an xdr buffer
.IP "subbuf" 12
the result buffer
.IP "base" 12
beginning of range in bytes
.IP "len" 12
length of range in bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
sets \fIsubbuf\fP to an xdr buffer representing the portion of \fIbuf\fP of
length \fIlen\fP starting at offset \fIbase\fP.

\fIbuf\fP and \fIsubbuf\fP may be pointers to the same struct xdr_buf.

Returns -1 if base of length are out of bounds.
